<br>
Mages can still summon the best pet. But Verant decided to make &quot;Situational&quot; pets. They did the same stinky thing to Necromancers. All Necro pets pre-50 were Warriors. Then at 53 we got a Rogue pet with half the health, almost no ac and hit for 2 points more than the 49 Warrior pet. (I'm not sure how familiar you are with the plight of Necro pets post-50 so I'll share some here.)<br>
<br>
At level 56 Necromancers got a &quot;Monk&quot; pet with a little better AC than the Rogue, not as much as the Warrior and hit for 4 more than the 49 Warrior pet, his health was only marginaly better than the 53 Rogue pet and WAY lower than the 49 Warrior pet. One of the things Verant gave the pets to allow them to survive ONE fear resist was a lifetap proc. This didn't work for well over a year and in fact was only fixed a few months ago. The proc would do damage to the mobs, but the pets weren't being healed by it. Necromancers were stuck using their level 49 Warrior pets in most cases because the other pets were quite broken and nothing that we asked for.<br>
<br>
So we had to get to level 59 and find one of the most rare spells in the game. Emmissary of Thule. At the time, he had 50 more hit points than the 49 Warrior pet and hit for LESS damage than the Monk pet and cost a Peridot and 2 bone chips to cast.<br>
<br>
Do you feel your Earth pet scales properly in power from level 4 to level 51? Is there some point where he takes a massive jump in power? Is there a point where he's a dissapointing upgrade from the previous Earth pet?<br>
<br>
That's the real question here.<br>
<br>
ALL Necro pets scaled in power just fine up to level 49. Then they took a HUGE nose dive. There should be a natural progression in power with ALL pets. If the level 49 Necromancer pet is in line with the 44 pet, then the 53 and 56 ones should be as well.<br>
<br>
Perhaps you are feeling the same sting of &quot;The Vision&quot; that decided all your pets shouldn't be tanks.<br>
<br>
I hope in the end they fix all pets to scale properly from level 1 to 60... the recent updates are certainly a step in the right direction and I'd like to say congrats to all of us.<br>
<br>
Thanks,<br>
Goji<br>
